<% help_title "Help on Global Search for Siemens Codes"%>
  <div class="container">
    <%= helpcrumbs %>
    <%= help_header %>
    <p class="lead">Find a code in any of the coding tables:</p>
    <p>The Siemens Code Search feature will search for the given code or part of the long text in the
      following tables:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><%= link_to_help 'function_codes', FunctionCode.model_name.human -%></li>
      <li><%= link_to_help 'service_codes', ServiceCode.model_name.human -%></li>
      <li><%= link_to_help 'product_codes', ProductCode.model_name.human -%></li>
      <li><%= link_to_help 'location_codes', LocationCode.model_name.human -%></li>
      <li><%= link_to_help 'phase_codes', PhaseCode.model_name.human -%></li>
      <li><%= link_to_help 'groups', Group.model_name.human -%></li>
    </ul>
    <p>Each of the above tables will be searched for the given code in
      the code field: The result will contain all codes
      starting with the given string. If the code-specific character prefix
      is omitted, all tables will be searched for the given code (ignoring
      the prefix character).</p>
    <p>When searching for a text, all labels in the above tables will 
      be searched if they include the specified string.</p>
    <p>Please be aware that the search is case-insensitive and that the
      search in the labels will search for <strong>any</strong>
      occurance in the label.</p>
    <%= help_footer FEATURE_ID_S_CODE_SEARCH %>
  </div> <!-- /container -->
